{"questionId":"9071680","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Graphing is an important tool in the study of rates of chemical reactions.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Outline why H<sub>3</sub>PO<sub>4</sub>/HPO<sub>4</sub><sup>2−</sup> is not a conjugate acid-base pair.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong>species<strong>» </strong>do not differ by a <strong>«</strong>single<strong>» </strong>proton/H<sup>+</sup></p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>conjugate base of H<sub>3</sub>PO<sub>4</sub> is H<sub>2</sub>PO<sub>4</sub><sup>–</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>not HPO<sub>4</sub><sup>2–</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>conjugate acid of HPO<sub>4</sub><sup>2–</sup> is H<sub>2</sub>PO<sub>4</sub><sup>–</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>not H<sub>3</sub>PO<sub>4</sub><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do </em><strong><em>not </em></strong><em>accept “hydrogen/H” for&nbsp;</em><em>“H</em><sup><em>+</em></sup><em>/proton”.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071680","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ2.d","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline why H3PO4/HPO42− is not a conjugate acid-base pair.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.1 Theories of acids and bases","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}